teacher_short_bio: Student at the Sephardic Rabbinical College
teacher_long_bio: Joseph Salem studied at Yeshivat Kiryat Moshe in Mitzpeh Yericho for two years where he had the opportunity to learn under the leadership of Rabbi Shabtai Sabato. He currently studies part time under Rabbi Shimon Alouf in the Sephardic Rabbinical College. In his day job, Joseph works in midtown Manhattan in the textile industry. He and his wife Loraine have 3 children, and hope to one day live in Eretz Yisrael.

teacher_short_bio: Teacher at Ahaba Ve Ahva
teacher_long_bio: Joey Soffer has studied for many years under both Rabbi Shimon Alouf and Rabbi Harold Sutton. He is currently teaching Daf Yomi, having made a siyum three previous times as both a student and a teacher. In his day job, Joey trades different types of securities, futures, and derivative contracts in the open markets. He and his wife Adelle have six children and live in Brooklyn, NY.
